––– comment –––
Small table no-tree path: no iterator planning happens, but the JSON expression alias still has to match.
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "SET GLOBAL secondary_indexes=1; SELECT id, IN (properties.channels, 29) AS p2 FROM gh4345_mini WHERE p2=1 LIMIT 0,1;"
––– output –––
+------+------+
| id   | p2   |
+------+------+
|    1 |    1 |
+------+------+
––– comment –––
Large no-tree path: with SI enabled this is the positive control, and with SI disabled it exercises fallback.
––– input –––
manticore-load --quiet --json --port=9306 --init="SET GLOBAL auto_optimize=0; DROP TABLE IF EXISTS gh4345_big_no_tree; CREATE TABLE gh4345_big_no_tree (id BIGINT, properties JSON secondary_index='1');" --load="INSERT INTO gh4345_big_no_tree (id,properties) VALUES (<increment>,'{\"loginName\":\"alpha\",\"subscriptions\":[],\"channels\":[29]}')" --batch-size=1000 --threads=2 --total=12000 > /dev/null; echo $?
––– output –––
0
––– input –––
mysql -h0 -P9306 -e "INSERT INTO gh4345_big_no_tree VALUES (12001, '{\"loginName\":\"alpha\",\"subscriptions\":[],\"channels\":[30]}'); FLUSH RAMCHUNK gh4345_big_no_tree; SHOW TABLE gh4345_big_no_tree STATUS LIKE 'disk_chunks';"
––– output –––
+---------------+-------+
| Variable_name | Value |
+---------------+-------+
| disk_chunks   | 1     |
+---------------+-------+
